parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
warning lights appear on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to move or only moves a short distance
the electrical system shuts down totally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retraction system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the seat belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract properly after being unbuckled
the seat belt remains stuck or tangled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer and odometer can lead to inaccurate speed readings, which can increase the risk of accidents or traffic violations, and may also affect the vehicle's overall performance and maintenance.
symptoms: The speedometer and odometer provide inaccurate readings
the speedometer fails to display an accurate speed rate
the odometer fails to display the correct mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission filter can cause the torque converter to fail, leading to transmission lock-up, loss of forward momentum, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission failure
torque converter failure
transmission lock-up
loss of forward momentum
inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to fail to shift, hit the rev limiter, and stop all forward momentum, leading to increased risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic.
symptoms: Vehicle fails to shift

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of warning and design flaw in the transmission shifting system can lead to accidents and safety issues, especially when the vehicle is marketed as an automatic but requires manual shifting in certain situations.
symptoms: No warning of transmission shifting issues
design flaw in transmission shifting system
inability to access shifters when turning
loss of control.
